import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Load data from Excel file
data = pd.read_excel('/app/data/workbench/spreadsheets/8cc22e7f-ba88-4e37-a1a8-dfba5c598715.xlsx', sheet_name='Game Observations')

# Prepare data for plotting
game_block_counts = data['Block'].value_counts()

# Create bar chart
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.set_theme(style='whitegrid', palette='viridis')
ax = sns.barplot(x=game_block_counts.index, y=game_block_counts.values)

# Add labels and title
ax.set_title('Count of Game Block Observations')
ax.set_xlabel('Block Type')
ax.set_ylabel('Count')

# Rotate x-axis labels for better readability
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

# Add data labels
for p in ax.patches:
    ax.annotate(f'{p.get_height():.0f}', (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2, p.get_height()),
                ha='center', va='baseline', xytext=(0, 10), textcoords='offset points')

# Adjust layout to prevent overlapping
plt.tight_layout()

# Display plot
plt.show()
